<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-06T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-06T17:00:00-05:00" n="163" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d163">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/9873</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-06T23:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 6, 1918, 11 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 7, 3.10
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3818. Department’s 3830, May 3, 4 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d163fn1">See footnote 1, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_222">p. 222</ref>.</note> In bringing this
                                matter to the attention of the Foreign Office today, Mr. <persName corresp="#p_PS1">Pichon</persName> said that it was his personal
                                opinion that such a declaration as to both Turkey and Bulgaria would
                                be of much help to the Allies. He, however, wishes to bring the
                                question before the Council of the Ministers tomorrow for their
                                consideration before undertaking to answer for the French
                                Government. As soon as I hear further from him I will telegraph his
                                answer.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SWG1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>